metadata.rowLabel: A unique record of a Terry Stop, as reported by the officer conducting the stop.

description:
This data represents records of police reported stops under Terry v. Ohio, 392 U.S. 1 (1968). Each row represents a unique stop. 

- Each record contains perceived demographics of the subject, as reported by the officer making the stop and officer demographics as reported to the Seattle Police Department, for employment purposes. 

- Where available, data elements from the associated Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event (e.g. Call Type, Initial Call Type, Final Call Type) are included.

columns.name: Subject Age Group
columns.description: Subject Age Group (10 year increments) as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Subject ID
columns.description: Key, generated daily, identifying unique subjects in the dataset using a character to character match of first name and last name. "Null" values indicate an "anonymous" or "unidentified" subject. Subjects of a Terry Stop are not required to present identification.

columns.name: GO / SC Num
columns.description: General Offense or Street Check number, relating the Terry Stop to the parent report. This field may have a one to many relationship in the data.

columns.name: Terry Stop ID
columns.description: Key identifying unique Terry Stop reports.

columns.name: Stop Resolution
columns.description: Resolution of the stop as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Weapon Type
columns.description: Type of weapon, if any, identified during a search or frisk of the subject. Indicates "None" if no weapons was found.

columns.name: Officer ID
columns.description: Key identifying unique officers in the dataset.

columns.name: Officer YOB
columns.description: Year of birth, as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Officer Gender
columns.description: Gender of the officer, as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Officer Race
columns.description: Race of the officer, as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Subject Perceived Race
columns.description: Perceived race of the subject, as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Subject Perceived Gender
columns.description: Perceived gender of the subject, as reported by the officer.

columns.name: Reported Date
columns.description: Date the report was filed in the Records Management System (RMS). Not necessarily the date the stop occurred but generally within 1 day.

columns.name: Reported Time
columns.description: Time the stop was reported in the Records Management System (RMS). Not the time the stop occurred but generally within 10 hours.

columns.name: Initial Call Type

top.item: ASLT - IP/JO - WITH OR W/O WPNS (NO SHOOTINGS)
DIST - IP/JO - DV DIST - NO ASLT
THEFT (DOES NOT INCLUDE SHOPLIFT OR SVCS)
ASLT - WITH OR W/O WEAPONS (NO SHOOTINGS)

columns.description: Initial classification of the call as assigned by 911.

columns.name: Final Call Type
columns.description: Final classification of the call as assigned by the primary officer closing the event.

columns.name: Call Type
columns.description: How the call was received by the communication center.

columns.name: Officer Squad
columns.description: Functional squad assignment (not budget) of the officer as reported by the Data Analytics Platform (DAP).

columns.name: Arrest Flag
columns.description: Indicator of whether a "physical arrest" was made, of the subject, during the Terry Stop. Does not necessarily reflect a report of an arrest in the Records Management System (RMS).

columns.name: Frisk Flag
columns.description: Indicator of whether a "frisk" was conducted, by the officer, of the subject, during the Terry Stop.

columns.name: Precinct
columns.description: Precinct of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.

columns.name: Sector
columns.description: Sector of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.

columns.name: Beat
columns.description: Beat of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.

name: Terry Stops
